  "prompt": "What is a good amount of money yearly to live more than comfortably in the USA?",
  "response": "The amount of money needed to live comfortably varies depending on factors like location, lifestyle, family size, and personal expenses. However, here's a general breakdown:\n\n1. National Average:\n- $75,000-$90,000 per year is often considered a comfortable salary for an individual\n- $100,000-$150,000 for a family of four\n\n2. By Region:\n- High-cost areas like San Francisco, New York City: $150,000-$250,000\n- Mid-range cities like Denver, Atlanta: $80,000-$120,000\n- Lower-cost areas like Midwest cities: $60,000-$80,000\n\n3. Considerations:\n- Housing costs\n- Cost of living\n- Personal debt\n- Lifestyle preferences\n- Savings goals\n\n4. Comfort Level Indicators:\n- Ability to save 10-20% of income\n- Afford rent/mortgage without stress\n- Cover unexpected expenses\n- Enjoy discretionary spending\n- Contribute to retirement\n\nRemember, \"comfortable\" is subjective and depends on individual circumstances. These are general guidelines, and actual needs can vary significantly based on personal situations.",
